DISCIPLE backed up and allowed TALON and TUCSON the chance to leave
undisturbed, his head is bowed and his eyes respectful. &quot;I hear you
old one.&quot; he said quietly. &quot;You are no more and I understand now and
so will Arcane.&quot;

He nodded respectfully, &quot;We will leave you as you left this place.&quot; he
looked up at the skies, &quot;However we must find a way to leave.&quot;

As TUCSON and TALON leave the area and arrive back at the ARK there
was a thoughtful almost sad look from DISCIPLE as he looked at the
other dragons present. &quot;The call from ARCANE is for all dragons, That
one has made his choice.&quot; He said quietly. &quot;You know what must be
done.&quot;

The other dragons nodded as they carefully looked around, as if
looking at the land one last time. Then, like a flock of large
predatory birds they took to the air and began to fly off, leaving
nothing left of their existence, save for the bones of the OLD ONE.

In the air the other dragons quickly disappear from sight, leaving
only a single large silver and black armored plate glinting in the sun
as it lay on the ground as if driven in like a sword or a nail.

